<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>You need to realize one thing.........</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Chris">Chris</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:09 p.m. 15/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> You need to realize one thing.........<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1441" TARGET=_self>What terrible INBALANCE... DRuid is way too overpowered! it is like the best pick! balance is needed</A> (Tarquin)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Classes were balance first and foremost for pve untility. None were ever meant to be balanced perfectly one on one vs other players. Changing classes just for pvp concerns isn't feasible for Verants goals in a mostly pve game. There will always be a best class.....period. There is no guarantee that a rogue will ever be able to compete with an Erudite wizard.

<P>&gt; I checked druid spells... He has soooo many spells like more
<BR>&gt; than pure spellcaster
<BR>He is a pure spellcaster.
<P>Meant to be. They are master of diversity, but not great at any one skill. It's going to be a fact that some classes will be more popular than others for 1 on 1 combat.
<P>&gt; he has heal
<BR>weaker than cleric heal
<BR>&gt; he has STRONG offensive DD spells
<BR>weaker than wizard or magician damage
<BR>&gt; +bind
<BR>all casters get it
<BR>&gt; +invises...
<BR>only outdoors and useless if your are being attacked(until later levels)
<BR>&gt; +root
<BR>agreed root spells suck in pvp
<BR>&gt; +defense + buff spells
<BR>not all that great, but you forgot to mention damage spells, those can hurt in pvp.
<BR>&gt; + HE can wear armor up to some level, like leather or better
<BR>They can wear leather. I know for a fact any armor worth wearing past leather equivalent is also available to wizards as well.
<BR>&gt; + he can wield a weapon !
<BR>Weapon skills, they are no better than any cleric or shamans, and exactly the same as any wizard until weapon skill caps come into play at later levels. People have some weird idea that druids are part warrior just because they can use a scimitar, its just some left over rp choice from D&D type games.
<P>&gt; what the.. i know Brad slowed down advancemenet of druids and
<BR>&gt; hybrids, but thats not the fix, that still makes them strongest
<BR>&gt; characters, doesn't it? I mean i know that 90% of my friends are
<BR>&gt; druids (sorry)... this is sorta not right I dont want to see
<BR>&gt; whole server with like 10 druids per any other type of class..
<P>Druids are no more hybrids than a cleric or shaman. If being the best is all that matter then play a druid if you deem it 'best'. I have found many other classes just as powerful in the right circumstances. It's all according to who starts the combat and under what conditions.
<P>laters, Chris
<P>btw, I agree some classes are more powerful, but I know that pve was always the balance intended, not pvp.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
